ccrual plans](./media/acc.gif)](./media/acc.gif) For more information about benefit accrual plans, see [Payroll data updates FAQ](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dynamics365/operations/financials/localizations/north-america/payroll-data-updates)."},{"pos":[1325,1356],"content":"Gather the required information","linkify":"Gather the required information","nodes":[{"content":"Gather the required information","pos":[0,31]}]},{"content":"A benefit accrual plan includes a set of rules that determine how hours in the plan accrue and are used.","pos":[1357,1461]},{"content":"The plan also includes a list of earning codes that are matched against the earning codes on earnings statement lines.","pos":[1462,1580]},{"content":"Therefore, the plan balance can be reduced when a specific earning code is used.","pos":[1581,1661]},{"content":"The rules for the plan are based on the number of months that a worker has been employed with the organization.","pos":[1662,1773]},{"content":"The months of employment are based on the employment start date or the seniority date.","pos":[1774,1860]},{"content":"You define rules to control the rate that benefits accrue at, and to control the maximum accrual limit, minimum balance, and carry-forward limit.","pos":[1861,2006]},{"pos":[2012,2019],"content":"Example","linkify":"Example","nodes":[{"content":"Example","pos":[0,7]}]},{"content":"Your paid time off (PTO) plan has three rates, which are based on years of employment.","pos":[2021,2107]},{"content":"Years of employment","pos":[2111,2130]},{"content":"PTO days per year","pos":[2142,2159]},{"content":"Fewer than 5","pos":[2217,2229]},{"content":"10","pos":[2248,2250]},{"content":"At least 5 but fewer than 10","pos":[2270,2298]},{"content":"15","pos":[2301,2303]},{"content":"At least 10","pos":[2323,2334]},{"content":"20","pos":[2354,2356]},{"content":"The benefit accrual is based on the years of employment.","pos":[2375,2431]},{"content":"For workers to accrue the correct total, you must convert the years of employment to months of employment.","pos":[2432,2538]},{"content":"You must also convert the number of PTO days per year to the number of PTO hours that accrue for every hour that is worked.","pos":[2539,2662]},{"content":"To convert the years of employment to months of employment, multiply the number of years by 12.","pos":[2663,2758]},{"content":"Here are the calculations for the example plan:","pos":[2759,2806]},{"content":"0 × 12 = 0 5 × 12 = 60 10 × 12 = 120","pos":[2808,2844]},{"content":"To convert the PTO days per year to the hourly accrual rate, multiply the number of days that accrue per year by the number of hours in a work day to get the number of hours that accrue per year.","pos":[2846,3041]},{"content":"Then divide that number by the number of hours that are worked in a year to get the hourly accrual rate.","pos":[3042,3146]},{"content":"The following formula will work for most workers: Number of days accrued per year × 8 hours worked in a day ÷ 2,080 hours worked in a year = Hourly accrual rate Here are the calculations for the example plan:","pos":[3147,3355]},{"content":"10 × 8 ÷ 2,080 = 0.03846 15 × 8 ÷ 2,080 = 0.05769 20 × 8 ÷ 2,080 = 0.07692","pos":[3357,3431]},{"content":"Enter these numbers into a table, as shown here, to make it easier for you to set up the plan rules.","pos":[3433,3533]},{"content":"Months of employment","pos":[3537,3557]},{"content":"Hourly accrual rate","pos":[3560,3579]},{"content":"0","pos":[3631,3632]},{"content":"0.03846","pos":[3654,3661]},{"content":"60","pos":[3678,3680]},{"content":"0.05769","pos":[3701,3708]},{"content":"120","pos":[3725,3728]},{"content":"0.07692","pos":[3748,3755]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Tip:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> You can use the hourly accrual rate to verify the amount that should accrue in each pay statement.","pos":[3771,3878],"source":"**Tip:** You can use the hourly accrual rate to verify the amount that should accrue in each pay statement."},{"content":"For example, if workers who accrue 15 days per year are paid biweekly, and they work 40 hours per week, multiply the hourly accrual rate of 0.05769 by 80 hours.","pos":[3879,4039]},{"content":"The result is 4.6152.","pos":[4040,4061]},{"content":"Therefore, the workers should accrue 4.6152 hours on each pay statement.","pos":[4062,4134]},{"pos":[4139,4167],"content":"Set up benefit accrual plans","linkify":"Set up benefit accrual plans","nodes":[{"content":"Set up benefit accrual plans","pos":[0,28]}]},{"pos":[4168,4275],"content":"To set up the benefit accrual plans, enter the following information on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Benefit accrual plans<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page.","source":"To set up the benefit accrual plans, enter the following information on the **Benefit accrual plans** page."},{"content":"Field","pos":[4380,4385]},{"content":"Description","pos":[4395,4406]},{"content":"Benefit accrual plan Description","pos":[4456,4488]},{"content":"The name and description for the plan.","pos":[4498,4536]},{"content":"Annual plan start date","pos":[4570,4592]},{"content":"The start date for the plan.","pos":[4602,4630]},{"content":"The plan is reset each year on the anniversary of this date.","pos":[4631,4691]},{"content":"If you leave this field blank, the plan isn’t reset.","pos":[4692,4744]},{"content":"Any fields that show data for the plan year, such as the <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Plan year accrued<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Plan year used<ept id=\"p2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> fields on the <bpt id=\"p3\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Benefit accrual balances<ept id=\"p3\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> page, will include all transactions from the start of the plan instead of all transactions in the plan year.","pos":[4745,5037],"source":" Any fields that show data for the plan year, such as the <strong>Plan year accrued</strong> and <strong>Plan year used</strong> fields on the <strong>Benefit accrual balances</strong> page, will include all transactions from the start of the plan instead of all transactions in the plan year."},{"content":"Carry forward balances","pos":[5070,5092]},{"content":"If you select this option, balances at the end of the plan year can be carried over to the next plan year.","pos":[5102,5208]},{"content":"When you create the plan rules, you can limit the number of hours that can be carried forward.","pos":[5209,5303]},{"content":"Accrual rate basis","pos":[5337,5355]},{"content":"The method that this plan uses to accrue benefits for workers who are enrolled in the plan.","pos":[5365,5456]},{"content":"The method is used together with the value in the <bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Amount or rate<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> field to determine the number of hours that are added to the worker’s plan.","pos":[5457,5614],"source":" The method is used together with the value in the <strong>Amount or rate</strong> field to determine the number of hours that are added to the worker’s plan."},{"content":"Select one of the following options:","pos":[5615,5651],"source":" Select one of the following options:\n"},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Hourly rate<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> – The number of hours that are added to the plan balance are calculated by multiplying the number of eligible hours on the pay statement by the rate in the <bpt id=\"p2\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Amount or rate<ept id=\"p2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> field.","pos":[5661,5884],"source":"<strong>Hourly rate</strong> – The number of hours that are added to the plan balance are calculated by multiplying the number of eligible hours on the pay statement by the rate in the <strong>Amount or rate</strong> field."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Fixed amount by payroll frequency<ept id=\"p1\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> – The number of hours in the <bpt id=\"p2\">&lt;strong&gt;</bpt>Amount or rate<ept id=\"p2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ept> field is added to the plan 