l rate basis is an hourly rate.","pos":[12823,12987]},{"content":"For example, in a plan where a worker accrues 80 hours each year, if the benefit accrues at an hourly rate, enter 0.03846.","pos":[12988,13110]},{"content":"If the benefit accrues as a fixed amount by date, enter 80.","pos":[13111,13170]},{"content":"The rate for compensatory time plans is entered on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Earning codes for plan accrual<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> FastTab.","pos":[13171,13269],"source":" The rate for compensatory time plans is entered on the **Earning codes for plan accrual** FastTab."},{"content":"Maximum accrual limit","pos":[14146,14167]},{"content":"The maximum number of hours that can accrue in the plan in a single plan year.","pos":[14170,14248]},{"content":"When this number is reached, no more hours accrue in the plan until the start of the next plan year, unless a manual adjustment reduces the accrued amount for the plan year.","pos":[14249,14422]},{"content":"If the plan isn't reset each year, this value is the maximum number of hours that can accrue over the life of the plan.","pos":[14423,14542]},{"content":"Minimum balance","pos":[15493,15508]},{"content":"The number of hours that must be available in the plan before a worker can use hours from the plan.","pos":[15517,15616]},{"content":"When the available balance is less than this number, the worker can’t use any hours from the plan until additional hours have accrued, or until the available balance has been adjusted.","pos":[15617,15801]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Tip:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> To let workers take time off before they have accrued the hours, enter a negative number.","pos":[15802,15900],"source":"**Tip:** To let workers take time off before they have accrued the hours, enter a negative number."},{"content":"If an earnings statement includes hours that will reduce the available balance in the plan to less than the minimum balance, the earnings statement lines that include those hours aren’t released.","pos":[15901,16096]},{"content":"Carry-forward limit","pos":[16840,16859]},{"content":"The highest number of hours that can be carried forward from one plan year to the next.","pos":[16864,16951]},{"content":"If the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Carry forward balances<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> option isn't selected, this field isn't available, and no hours are carried forward.","pos":[16952,17070],"source":" If the **Carry forward balances** option isn't selected, this field isn't available, and no hours are carried forward."},{"content":"The earning codes that are entered on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Earning codes for plan usage<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> FastTab are used to verify the available balance when an earnings statement that includes the earning code is released.","pos":[18190,18384],"source":"The earning codes that are entered on the **Earning codes for plan usage** FastTab are used to verify the available balance when an earnings statement that includes the earning code is released."},{"content":"The codes are also used to reduce the plan balance when a pay statement line that includes the earning code is submitted for payment.","pos":[18385,18518]},{"content":"If you use the earning code for a benefit accrual on an earnings statement for a worker who isn't enrolled in the plan, no validation occurs.","pos":[18523,18664]},{"content":"The earning codes that are entered on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Earning codes for plan accrual<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> FastTab are used to increase the plan balance when a pay statement line that includes the earning code is submitted for payment.","pos":[18669,18874],"source":"The earning codes that are entered on the **Earning codes for plan accrual** FastTab are used to increase the plan balance when a pay statement line that includes the earning code is submitted for payment."},{"content":"For example, you enter an earning code for regular hours here.","pos":[18875,18937]},{"content":"If that earning code is used 